3. cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) - The paper uses data from an online location-based social network, which could potentially have implications for cybersecurity and privacy. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses a large dataset and proposes a model to generate social networks, which involves algorithms and data structures. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper examines the relationship between physical places and social ties, which could have implications for human-computer interaction and the design of location-based social networks.
